The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 August is 62,379 (7,189.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 August, there were 2,563 new confirmed cases (295.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 August, there were 2,441 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (122 extra cases).
